abstract: A look back at the day's best from Week 5 in college football.
snippet: A look back at the day's best from Week 5 in college football.
lead_paragraph: NATHAN SCHEELHAASE The Illinois quarterback passed for a career-high 391 yards, then scored on a 1-yard run with 13 seconds left to lead the No. 24 Illini to a 38-35 win over Northwestern. A. J. Jenkins caught 12 balls for a team-record 268 yards and 3 touchdowns.

headline.main: The Day's Best in College Football
